1
00:00:00,470 --> 00:00:02,070
(All characters, locations,
organizations, and incidents...)

2
00:00:02,070 --> 00:00:03,410
(in this drama are fictional.)

3
00:00:03,410 --> 00:00:04,940
(This production followed
all guidelines for young actors.)

4
00:00:06,950 --> 00:00:08,350
I'll bury the video...

5
00:00:08,810 --> 00:00:10,850
so it's not seen ever again.
In return...

6
00:00:11,680 --> 00:00:12,680
In return?

7
00:00:12,820 --> 00:00:14,320
Prevent Chairman Gong Nan Sook...

8
00:00:15,350 --> 00:00:16,520
from being arrested.

9
00:00:18,760 --> 00:00:21,060
It's very interesting.

10
00:00:22,660 --> 00:00:24,760
Someone's life is on the line here.

11
00:00:25,830 --> 00:00:27,600
But to you, it's just a game,
isn't it?

12
00:00:29,170 --> 00:00:30,840
But why should I trust you?

13
00:00:31,570 --> 00:00:33,540
How do I know
you won't just release...

14
00:00:35,110 --> 00:00:36,910
the video of me killing Cha Ki Beom?

15
00:00:37,080 --> 00:00:38,910
It doesn't matter
if you believe me or not.

16
00:00:39,440 --> 00:00:40,810
You'll have to do what I say.

17
00:00:41,380 --> 00:00:44,880
Or else I'll release the video
right here and now.

18
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:46,620
You really think
you'll get the chance?

19
00:00:52,760 --> 00:00:54,590
I may have failed last time,

20
00:00:55,790 --> 00:00:57,560
but what if I get rid of you
right now?

21
00:00:57,830 --> 00:00:59,400
You don't think I came prepared?

22
00:01:01,270 --> 00:01:04,640
If I don't press the cancel button
by 8 a.m. tomorrow,

23
00:01:05,040 --> 00:01:08,640
it's scheduled to post automatically
on social media.

24
00:01:20,990 --> 00:01:21,990
Sir!

25
00:01:22,050 --> 00:01:23,890
What is your response
to the investigation?

26
00:01:24,420 --> 00:01:25,420
Is it true?

27
00:01:27,790 --> 00:01:28,790
Please step aside.

28
00:01:28,960 --> 00:01:30,060
Move back!

29
00:01:30,630 --> 00:01:32,300
- Move aside.
- What are you going to do?

30
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:36,000
Mr. Chairman!

31
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:40,000
(Breaking News: Kunhyang Chairman
Jin Tae Seok Arrested for Murder)

32
00:01:40,210 --> 00:01:41,770
- Move aside.
- What are you going to do?

33
00:01:42,540 --> 00:01:43,710
Coming through.

34
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:47,250
- Just give us one comment!
- Chairman Jin!

35
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:53,750
You'll have to do what I say.

36
00:01:54,390 --> 00:01:57,960
Or else I'll release the video
right here and now.

37
00:02:02,560 --> 00:02:04,030
(Episode 87)

38
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:08,830
My whole body aches.

39
00:02:08,830 --> 00:02:10,670
Chairman Gong!

40
00:02:11,900 --> 00:02:14,010
Why didn't you give me a heads-up?

41
00:02:14,740 --> 00:02:16,270
Goodness, what happened to your eye?

42
00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:18,110
You must have been through a lot.

43
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:21,210
You must have really missed me,
Manager Gu.

44
00:02:21,680 --> 00:02:23,750
Yes, I missed you.

45
00:02:24,420 --> 00:02:27,250
Are you learning English
in your spare time?

46
00:02:27,620 --> 00:02:30,120
You have too much time.
I should just smack you.

47
00:02:32,890 --> 00:02:34,690
Thank you, Vice Chairman Joo,

48
00:02:35,030 --> 00:02:36,830
for bringing Chairman Gong
back to me.

49
00:02:37,560 --> 00:02:38,730
I hardly did anything.

50
00:02:39,730 --> 00:02:41,200
Madam Gong is the one who suffered
in that cold place.

51
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:43,670
And my Ha Neul even came out
to meet me.

52
00:02:44,140 --> 00:02:48,240
I guess this is why they say
raising a good son is so rewarding.

53
00:02:49,110 --> 00:02:50,680
Anyway, where is that girl,
Young Chae?

54
00:02:50,940 --> 00:02:54,710
Her mother just avoided jail
thanks to her brother,

55
00:02:54,780 --> 00:02:56,310
and she can't even be bothered
to show her face.

56
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:59,080
You're home.

57
00:03:01,790 --> 00:03:03,350
What happened...

58
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:05,660
You went to a holding cell
in a mink coat?

59
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,860
Seriously, you're one of a kind.

60
00:03:09,130 --> 00:03:12,330
Never mind all that.
What's with you? You look awful.

61
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:15,170
Did you just wake up at my house?

62
00:03:15,170 --> 00:03:16,370
He found everything out.

63
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:19,370
Se Hoon kicked me out.

64
00:03:19,370 --> 00:03:21,870
What? You'll be the death of me.

65
00:03:21,970 --> 00:03:25,580
You got kicked out
as soon as I left?

66
00:03:26,340 --> 00:03:28,510
I swear, I can't take it.
I really can't.

67
00:03:29,250 --> 00:03:31,520
Anyway, I'm too hungry
to deal with this now.

68
00:03:31,720 --> 00:03:32,750
You should eat something.

69
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:35,090
I've already prepared it.

70
00:03:35,090 --> 00:03:38,360
Grandma told me
that you were being released.

71
00:03:38,490 --> 00:03:43,060
Grandma's the best, as always.
She knew what I'd be craving, right?

72
00:03:43,230 --> 00:03:45,300
So what is it? What did you make?

73
00:03:50,970 --> 00:03:53,940
Look at all this.
It's a whole banquet of tofu.

74
00:03:54,270 --> 00:03:57,840
So you're just openly treating me
like a con fresh out of the joint.

75
00:03:58,040 --> 00:04:00,580
I just follow Grandma's orders
in the kitchen.

76
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:07,450
Just eat up.

77
00:04:07,450 --> 00:04:09,420
And from now on,
try not to end up in a cell again.

78
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:17,330
Maybe it's because my son served me.
Even plain tofu tastes amazing.

79
00:04:20,130 --> 00:04:21,230
Hey, Chef Hong,

80
00:04:21,830 --> 00:04:24,470
do you know why people eat tofu
after getting out of jail?

81
00:04:24,670 --> 00:04:25,800
What a strange thing
to be curious about.

82
00:04:26,740 --> 00:04:27,870
I've always wondered that, too.

83
00:04:29,340 --> 00:04:32,010
Just eat this tofu patty.

84
00:04:33,610 --> 00:04:37,550
Once a bean is ground to make tofu,
it can never return to being a bean.

85
00:04:38,050 --> 00:04:41,090
It's a symbol of washing away
your past mistakes and a promise...

86
00:04:41,450 --> 00:04:43,820
to never go back to your old ways.

87
00:04:44,390 --> 00:04:46,460
Hey, shut it.

88
00:04:46,460 --> 00:04:48,430
Are you really rubbing it in?

89
00:04:48,930 --> 00:04:51,200
I'm not some hardened criminal,
you know.

90
00:04:51,330 --> 00:04:53,260
Now it's Chef Hong speaking,
actually.

91
00:04:53,260 --> 00:04:55,230
Please enjoy your tofu dishes.

92
00:04:56,030 --> 00:04:57,870
He's so infuriating.

93
00:04:58,170 --> 00:04:59,770
He knocks me down,
then offers me tofu.

94
00:05:05,010 --> 00:05:06,080
What about me?

95
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,550
Go on, eat.

96
00:05:13,320 --> 00:05:14,690
So, I suppose Chairman Gong is out.

97
00:05:17,660 --> 00:05:21,130
I wonder what she means to Ha Neul.

98
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,230
His mother?

99
00:05:24,230 --> 00:05:25,660
No matter what she's done,

100
00:05:26,330 --> 00:05:27,570
even though she's not
his birth mother,

101
00:05:28,570 --> 00:05:31,440
could anyone treat her
the way he does?

102
00:05:32,740 --> 00:05:34,340
Not just anyone could do that.

103
00:05:35,740 --> 00:05:38,580
And what am I to you, Jung Won?

104
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:41,710
You are my mother.

105
00:05:43,150 --> 00:05:47,320
I can't quite sort out
my feelings yet, though.

106
00:05:48,050 --> 00:05:51,990
I don't think giving birth to you
automatically makes me your mother.

107
00:05:52,290 --> 00:05:55,160
I'm trying to earn the right
to be your mother,

108
00:05:55,560 --> 00:05:58,560
- and I'm trying my best.
- I know.

109
00:05:59,530 --> 00:06:03,200
I know how difficult and monumental
that is.

110
00:06:05,840 --> 00:06:08,910
You might have to give up everything
you've worked so hard to build.

111
00:06:10,510 --> 00:06:11,610
Are you still okay with that?

112
00:06:14,550 --> 00:06:16,510
My whole life has been
full of regrets.

113
00:06:18,450 --> 00:06:20,180
I don't want to repeat that
ever again.

114
00:06:22,220 --> 00:06:25,390
I always thought your life
was peaceful and happy.

115
00:06:26,460 --> 00:06:29,290
I thought you never wanted
to look back at the past.

116
00:06:31,300 --> 00:06:34,830
I thought so too,
until you came along, Jung Won.

117
00:06:35,170 --> 00:06:36,630
Because of me,

118
00:06:37,600 --> 00:06:39,040
your life has become harder.

119
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:41,040
Thanks to you,

120
00:06:41,840 --> 00:06:43,410
I feel like I've been born again.

121
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:46,080
You might call it
a foolish choice later,

122
00:06:47,180 --> 00:06:48,910
and you might come to regret it.

123
00:06:49,480 --> 00:06:51,050
No, it's the complete opposite.

124
00:06:51,950 --> 00:06:55,290
As long as I can protect you,
I'm not afraid of anything.

125
00:06:56,190 --> 00:06:57,390
Not even Jin Tae Seok.

126
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:01,530
To me, my father...

127
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:04,460
is one person and one person only.

128
00:07:05,830 --> 00:07:09,170
I want to clear my dad's name.

129
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:11,970
To prove his innocence?

130
00:07:18,140 --> 00:07:21,550
Are you sure you won't regret
getting Gong Nan Sook released?

131
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:24,320
It's one step back
to take ten steps forward.

132
00:07:24,620 --> 00:07:27,220
Chairman Han is backing Joo Ha Neul.

133
00:07:27,220 --> 00:07:28,290
And so is Cha Jung Won.

134
00:07:29,490 --> 00:07:32,360
How can you say that
when Hye Ra cherished you so much?

135
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:36,290
- She loved you more than your mom.
- Stop it.

136
00:07:37,360 --> 00:07:41,700
Do you think I've forgotten
what you did to my mother,

137
00:07:41,770 --> 00:07:43,270
using Chairman Gong Nan Sook
as your front?

138
00:07:44,400 --> 00:07:45,570
That's all in the past.

139
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:49,940
It's best to leave the past buried.
Hye Ra and I agreed on that.

140
00:07:50,010 --> 00:07:52,140
Is that why you accepted
Cha Jung Won?

141
00:07:52,380 --> 00:07:53,910
After you tried to have her killed
so many times?

142
00:07:56,250 --> 00:07:57,920
This is all Chairman Han's scheme!

143
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:59,820
Hye Ra is your only mother.

144
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:03,890
I won't let anyone badmouth Hye Ra.
Not even you, Se Hoon.

145
00:08:04,890 --> 00:08:06,490
I can see it perfectly clear,

146
00:08:07,260 --> 00:08:08,960
but it seems you're blind to it.

147
00:08:09,660 --> 00:08:12,530
- Han Hye Ra's true intentions.
- Shut up!

148
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:16,070
Says the man who didn't even know
his wife faked her pregnancy.

149
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:34,290
Why did you help me?

150
00:08:34,890 --> 00:08:37,320
Help you? Don't get the wrong idea.

151
00:08:38,020 --> 00:08:39,790
To take down Jin Tae Seok,

152
00:08:40,690 --> 00:08:42,660
I simply needed your power.

153
00:08:43,030 --> 00:08:46,560
Did Hye Ra and Jung Won agree
to getting me out?

154
00:08:47,270 --> 00:08:48,270
Yes.

155
00:08:51,470 --> 00:08:54,010
I know. If I were in your shoes,

156
00:08:54,070 --> 00:08:56,940
putting up with me wouldn't be easy.

157
00:08:58,580 --> 00:09:00,310
That's unusually self-aware of you.

158
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:04,450
It was only for a day,
but being stuck in a jail cell...

159
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:06,380
gave me a lot to think about.

160
00:09:07,990 --> 00:09:10,390
I know this may be hard for you,

161
00:09:10,690 --> 00:09:13,690
but if I had never met
Joo Sang Cheol,

162
00:09:14,130 --> 00:09:19,160
I might not have turned
into the worst witch on earth.

163
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:20,630
That's just an excuse.

164
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,600
A cowardly one.

165
00:09:22,670 --> 00:09:25,740
What are you talking about?
I am anything but a coward.

166
00:09:26,300 --> 00:09:29,370
Have you forgotten my nicknames?
Gong the Genius,

167
00:09:29,770 --> 00:09:32,410
Gong the Honest,
Gong the World's Greatest Woman,

168
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:34,110
and to top it off,
Gong the Guiltless.

169
00:09:35,110 --> 00:09:37,110
You aren't exactly guiltless,
to be honest.

170
00:09:37,620 --> 00:09:40,080
Fair enough.
But it's just a nickname!

171
00:09:41,420 --> 00:09:42,820
What do you want to do
about Jin Tae Seok?

172
00:09:43,020 --> 00:09:46,960
Tearing him apart limb from limb
wouldn't even begin to satisfy me.

173
00:09:47,260 --> 00:09:49,960
How dare he even think
of throwing me in jail?

174
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:53,730
Jin Tae Seok
will definitely retaliate.

175
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:56,300
Retaliate? Please.
I'm going to strike him first.

176
00:09:56,370 --> 00:09:58,170
Jin Tae Seok is planning
to pin the death...

177
00:09:58,240 --> 00:10:01,370
of Jin Se Hoon's birth mother
on you.

178
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:03,940
So he's trying to cut me loose?

179
00:10:04,210 --> 00:10:06,840
I'm not the type
to just stand by and watch.

180
00:10:07,180 --> 00:10:09,250
I'll drag him down with me...

181
00:10:09,250 --> 00:10:11,320
and chase him
to the end of the earth.

182
00:10:11,450 --> 00:10:13,820
That jerk, Jin Tae Seok.

183
00:10:15,090 --> 00:10:16,650
Mom, I need to talk to you.

184
00:10:18,660 --> 00:10:21,160
- Hurry.
- Hey, Ha Neul.

185
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:24,230
Hey! Stop! My whole body is aching!

186
00:10:24,300 --> 00:10:27,130
- You brat. Careful with the door.
- Come on.

187
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:30,300
It hurts! You little brat!

188
00:10:30,970 --> 00:10:32,500
What is it?

189
00:10:32,570 --> 00:10:34,210
I'm exhausted right now.

190
00:10:34,410 --> 00:10:37,910
My dark circles are down to my chin,
and they're at my ankles.

191
00:10:37,910 --> 00:10:39,610
That's because you haven't slept.

192
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:42,380
Solve my problem, then you can get
a good sleep and be pretty again.

193
00:10:42,450 --> 00:10:44,680
You brat. If you weren't my kid,
I swear I'd...

194
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,180
Then why did you have to get caught?

195
00:10:46,250 --> 00:10:48,090
If you get caught, you play dumb.

196
00:10:48,090 --> 00:10:49,420
You said I could do what I want!

197
00:10:49,490 --> 00:10:52,590
So you told Jin Se Hoon everything
and got kicked out?

198
00:10:52,590 --> 00:10:55,890
So, what did he say
when he kicked you out?

199
00:10:56,230 --> 00:10:59,000
He said I'm like him
and feels sorry,

200
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,770
and he needs time to think.

201
00:11:00,830 --> 00:11:01,830
He did?

202
00:11:02,300 --> 00:11:04,200
Give him some time, then.

203
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:06,370
Who knows? You could be soulmates,

204
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:09,210
or a pair of cockroaches.

205
00:11:09,210 --> 00:11:10,670
How can you say that
to your daughter?

206
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:14,110
If I succeed,
you won't go through this again.

207
00:11:14,180 --> 00:11:16,650
You and your big mouth...

208
00:11:16,650 --> 00:11:18,920
Getting kicked out is one thing,

209
00:11:18,980 --> 00:11:21,790
but why aren't you at work?
It's way past lunchtime.

210
00:11:22,250 --> 00:11:23,320
I don't want to go.

211
00:11:23,390 --> 00:11:25,260
Go to work,
or you'll get fired from there too.

212
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:27,730
I told you I took the day off
because you were getting out.

213
00:11:27,790 --> 00:11:29,230
Don't make me laugh.

214
00:11:29,230 --> 00:11:32,560
As if you were so worried and happy.

215
00:11:32,630 --> 00:11:35,830
You think I didn't know you waited
so I'd solve your problems?

216
00:11:36,100 --> 00:11:37,800
That's what you should do for me.

217
00:11:37,870 --> 00:11:40,100
This is why they say no kids
is a blessing.

218
00:11:40,340 --> 00:11:41,340
No, wait.

219
00:11:41,410 --> 00:11:44,110
I have my wonderful son, Ha Neul.

220
00:11:44,410 --> 00:11:45,810
So there, you little brat.

221
00:11:45,940 --> 00:11:47,710
You're so annoying!

222
00:11:49,010 --> 00:11:50,050
Why you...

223
00:11:51,580 --> 00:11:53,020
My whole body aches, seriously!

224
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:55,220
(Kunhyang Group)

225
00:12:01,630 --> 00:12:04,660
You're tall and slim,
so everything looks good on you.

226
00:12:04,660 --> 00:12:06,130
I know.

227
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:09,530
You should seriously be a model.

228
00:12:09,630 --> 00:12:12,040
It's not like you have any talent
for design, anyway.

229
00:12:12,270 --> 00:12:13,600
I agree.

230
00:12:13,670 --> 00:12:15,910
Did you forget
the new collection was my design?

231
00:12:17,110 --> 00:12:19,680
It's good enough
to be in a Paris collection now.

232
00:12:19,940 --> 00:12:21,580
And you still say I have no talent?

233
00:12:22,950 --> 00:12:24,520
Is it really your design?

234
00:12:26,220 --> 00:12:27,690
I'll ask you one last time.

235
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:30,190
Did you really design it yourself?

236
00:12:32,020 --> 00:12:33,260
It's mine.

237
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:36,460
A piece I completed
with my own two hands.

238
00:12:38,700 --> 00:12:41,700
Did I turn you into this?

239
00:12:42,770 --> 00:12:46,070
If I'd exposed what you did then
and set things right,

240
00:12:46,670 --> 00:12:48,270
would you be a different person now?

241
00:12:49,710 --> 00:12:51,180
What kind of nonsense
are you talking about?

242
00:12:52,110 --> 00:12:53,740
You were always jealous of me.

243
00:12:53,740 --> 00:12:55,910
You always coveted what was mine
and tried to take it.

244
00:12:56,750 --> 00:12:58,120
Not anymore.

245
00:12:58,820 --> 00:13:00,650
Just you watch.
I won't let you steal from me again.

246
00:13:05,760 --> 00:13:08,130
I think she actually believes
it's her design.

247
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:10,960
Is that what they call
Ripley's syndrome?

248
00:13:14,370 --> 00:13:16,000
(Joo Ha Neul)

249
00:13:22,270 --> 00:13:25,010
You should've taken Gong Nan Sook
down sooner...

250
00:13:25,840 --> 00:13:27,240
if you didn't want to die
like a dog.

251
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:32,280
He's still alive.

252
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,360
Make it look like
that punk Cha Ki Beom did it.

253
00:13:52,100 --> 00:13:54,940
We have him on tape saying
he should frame Cha Ki Beom.

254
00:13:55,010 --> 00:13:57,510
Is this recording enough
to request a retrial?

255
00:13:57,610 --> 00:13:59,580
It's possible, but...

256
00:14:00,040 --> 00:14:03,110
- Why? Is it not enough?
- It's only circumstantial evidence.

257
00:14:03,480 --> 00:14:06,950
I can't guarantee
you'll win the case.

258
00:14:08,950 --> 00:14:13,090
The other side will attack
the recording's credibility.

259
00:14:13,160 --> 00:14:15,460
So we need more concrete evidence.

260
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:16,460
Yes.

261
00:14:17,730 --> 00:14:20,630
Please tell us exactly what we need.

262
00:14:20,700 --> 00:14:22,530
A confession from the real culprit,
Jin Tae Seok.

263
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:26,740
It's a 25-year-old case,
so there's no evidence at the scene.

264
00:14:26,970 --> 00:14:30,270
And right now, that would be
your strongest piece of evidence.

265
00:14:30,770 --> 00:14:33,880
The next best thing would be
an eyewitness testimony.

266
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:36,280
We have a witness.

267
00:14:38,480 --> 00:14:40,250
What should I do with the body?

268
00:14:41,150 --> 00:14:42,420
Manager Hwang.

269
00:14:52,800 --> 00:14:54,870
Manager Hwang was there.

270
00:14:55,100 --> 00:14:57,870
If he testifies as a witness,
we have a chance of winning.

271
00:14:58,270 --> 00:15:00,600
Right. Manager Hwang was there.

272
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:02,770
I'll make Jin Tae Seok confess.

273
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:04,640
What?

274
00:15:05,410 --> 00:15:09,910
That he hurt Ha Neul's father
and framed my dad for it,

275
00:15:10,410 --> 00:15:13,280
I'll make him admit it himself
in front of everyone.

276
00:15:14,790 --> 00:15:16,050
Is that even possible?

277
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,760
I'll make it possible.

278
00:15:21,930 --> 00:15:23,330
On a day like today,

279
00:15:23,390 --> 00:15:27,130
I should just be sleeping soundly
all day long.

280
00:15:28,630 --> 00:15:30,830
But the faces of everyone
I need to pay back...

281
00:15:30,830 --> 00:15:33,040
keep popping into my head,

282
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:36,470
so I can't get a single
wink of sleep.

283
00:15:38,910 --> 00:15:41,150
Channel that anger
into getting your revenge.

284
00:15:42,910 --> 00:15:44,320
You're here.

285
00:15:44,450 --> 00:15:47,180
Oh my goodness.

286
00:15:48,120 --> 00:15:52,660
I must have really been through it.
I'm actually glad to see you.

287
00:15:53,760 --> 00:15:55,590
This is the part where you say,
"Thank you."

288
00:15:55,690 --> 00:15:58,800
Fine. Thank you.

289
00:15:58,900 --> 00:16:00,700
Don't thank me.

290
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:02,300
Thank Vice Chairman Joo Ha Neul.

291
00:16:02,770 --> 00:16:05,340
Right? My Ha Neul was the one
who pushed hardest...

292
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:06,870
to get me out, wasn't he?

293
00:16:08,310 --> 00:16:09,710
Okay, that's enough
of the touching reunion.

294
00:16:10,670 --> 00:16:12,440
To get you out of there,

295
00:16:12,980 --> 00:16:15,080
do you have any idea
what we had to give Jin Tae Seok?

296
00:16:15,950 --> 00:16:18,520
What did you give him?

297
00:16:18,520 --> 00:16:20,880
The video of what happened
at the gallery.

298
00:16:21,790 --> 00:16:25,360
How could you give that to him?
We needed that to take him down!

299
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:27,190
But more than the chance
to take him down,

300
00:16:27,890 --> 00:16:30,390
we needed your power even more.

301
00:16:30,460 --> 00:16:33,500
Don't tell me
the original was handed over to him.

302
00:16:33,560 --> 00:16:36,030
It hasn't been leaked to the world,

303
00:16:37,630 --> 00:16:39,440
but it won't stay hidden forever.

304
00:16:40,100 --> 00:16:43,140
Jin Tae Seok will pay
for what he's done.

305
00:16:43,140 --> 00:16:44,640
We'll make sure of it.

306
00:16:44,910 --> 00:16:46,780
You don't have to tell me twice.

307
00:16:47,180 --> 00:16:48,210
Let's do it.

308
00:16:51,180 --> 00:16:54,020
Anyway,
you'll just leave Young Chae...

309
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:55,420
after she got kicked out?

310
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:58,420
That's for Se Hoon to figure out.

311
00:16:58,920 --> 00:17:01,060
That stupid girl.
Why did she have to get caught?

312
00:17:03,590 --> 00:17:06,500
What? Stop staring.
I might start to like you.

313
00:17:06,560 --> 00:17:08,100
Look at me.

314
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:11,170
Young Chae's fake pregnancy...

315
00:17:11,940 --> 00:17:13,940
was your idea, wasn't it,
Gong Nan Sook?

316
00:17:16,040 --> 00:17:19,710
Jin Se Hoon, that brat!
I swear, I'll teach him...

317
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:24,310
What is it with that father and son?
Do they have a vendetta against us?

318
00:17:24,380 --> 00:17:26,720
How dare they do this to my family?

319
00:17:28,220 --> 00:17:29,390
You're reaping what you sow.

320
00:17:30,990 --> 00:17:33,690
Han Hye Ra. I've had enough of this.

321
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:36,730
You can stay and have some tea.
I have somewhere to be.

322
00:17:36,790 --> 00:17:37,800
What?

323
00:17:46,570 --> 00:17:49,910
It'll warm your body
and put your mind at ease.

324
00:17:51,010 --> 00:17:52,340
I heard she's the real deal.

325
00:17:52,580 --> 00:17:55,110
My grandma won't see anyone
but Chairman Gong Nan Sook...

326
00:17:57,250 --> 00:17:59,750
Oh my, what's gotten into Grandma
all of a sudden?

327
00:18:01,490 --> 00:18:05,520
You poor thing,
living as the most feared woman.

328
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:07,190
You must have gone through so much.

329
00:18:08,060 --> 00:18:09,560
What are we going to do?

330
00:18:09,560 --> 00:18:12,430
Chef Hong, what's wrong?

331
00:18:12,500 --> 00:18:15,730
You'll end up giving your life
for your child.

332
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:19,240
My heart breaks. It's devastating.

333
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:20,870
If that's what it takes,

334
00:18:22,510 --> 00:18:24,010
then that's what I have to do.

335
00:18:25,610 --> 00:18:26,780
That's what it means to be a mother.

336
00:18:34,850 --> 00:18:35,850
What's going on?

337
00:18:36,550 --> 00:18:38,320
Hey,
didn't you say you'd include me?

338
00:18:39,860 --> 00:18:43,130
I have to prove
that Jin Tae Seok killed my father.

339
00:18:44,360 --> 00:18:45,530
Please, help me.

340
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:48,870
Without a witness testimony,

341
00:18:48,930 --> 00:18:52,070
it'll be hard to prove
my dad's innocence.

342
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:55,540
It's the only way we can get
a confession out of Jin Tae Seok.

343
00:18:55,610 --> 00:18:58,780
At the scene
where Vice Chairman Joo's dad died,

344
00:18:58,940 --> 00:19:00,680
you were there, Manager Hwang?

345
00:19:01,610 --> 00:19:03,910
- Yes.
- Then why are you hesitating?

346
00:19:04,350 --> 00:19:05,880
Didn't you promise
you'd be my friend?

347
00:19:06,450 --> 00:19:08,220
Yes, I did.

348
00:19:08,220 --> 00:19:09,620
Think about my daughter,
Jo Jung Won.

349
00:19:10,050 --> 00:19:13,060
Have you already forgotten
how she died?

350
00:19:14,460 --> 00:19:15,560
I understand.

351
00:19:16,190 --> 00:19:19,660
I'll help you,
Vice Chairman Joo and Cha Jung Won.

352
00:19:20,430 --> 00:19:22,030
You'd better put your life
on the line.

353
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:24,700
Or else, I'll beat you to a pulp.

354
00:19:24,770 --> 00:19:28,540
Yes. I'll put my life on the line
to help you.

355
00:19:33,340 --> 00:19:37,310
(Se Mi)

356
00:19:51,330 --> 00:19:52,360
Se Mi.

357
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:54,530
This must be so hard on you.

358
00:19:55,570 --> 00:19:58,340
I don't know what to do, Jung Won.

359
00:20:04,880 --> 00:20:06,510
Can you help me?

360
00:20:08,250 --> 00:20:09,350
Me?

361
00:20:09,350 --> 00:20:11,110
If you know
Jin Tae Seok was wrong...

362
00:20:11,550 --> 00:20:14,950
I mean, if you know your father
was wrong,

363
00:20:15,850 --> 00:20:17,020
you have to speak up.

364
00:20:17,620 --> 00:20:18,760
You have to make things right.

365
00:20:20,090 --> 00:20:22,560
I know you can do it, Se Mi.

366
00:20:27,630 --> 00:20:30,230
(Vice President Jin Se Hoon)

367
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:37,810
When I saw Cha Jung Won take my name
and my place, living with you,

368
00:20:38,210 --> 00:20:40,410
I realized what I needed to have.

369
00:20:41,450 --> 00:20:44,280
- It was you, Jin Se Hoon.
- I understand that feeling.

370
00:20:45,220 --> 00:20:48,020
But you deceived me completely.

371
00:20:48,120 --> 00:20:50,520
I loved that you were slowly opening
your heart to me,

372
00:20:50,690 --> 00:20:53,660
thinking that I was
actually carrying A Reum,

373
00:20:54,460 --> 00:20:55,890
and I was so grateful.

374
00:21:01,870 --> 00:21:05,470
Hey! Who do you think you are,
kicking out my Young Chae?

375
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:07,170
How was the holding cell?

376
00:21:08,310 --> 00:21:09,910
Did you get a good night's sleep?

377
00:21:10,370 --> 00:21:13,180
You're actually looking
better than ever.

378
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:17,580
Your one and only mother-in-law
barely avoided going to prison,

379
00:21:17,650 --> 00:21:19,980
so what's with that crappy attitude?

380
00:21:20,280 --> 00:21:22,150
You were the one
who pushed Young Chae...

381
00:21:22,650 --> 00:21:24,250
to fake her pregnancy, right?

382
00:21:24,250 --> 00:21:26,420
I was desperate! What was I to do?

383
00:21:28,630 --> 00:21:32,430
But Young Chae's feelings
for you are real.

384
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:35,400
And you'd have to be an idiot
not to have noticed.

385
00:21:36,230 --> 00:21:39,570
And you two can just
have a baby for real, can't you?

386
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:41,140
You always make everything
sound so simple.

387
00:21:42,210 --> 00:21:45,740
You're deluded enough to think
the world revolves around you.

388
00:21:46,710 --> 00:21:47,980
Let me ask you one thing.

389
00:21:48,710 --> 00:21:50,950
Do you really find my Young Chae
that unappealing?

390
00:21:51,010 --> 00:21:53,650
Is the very sight of her
that unbearable?

391
00:21:58,460 --> 00:22:00,620
I'll give you exactly two days.

392
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:04,390
It won't hurt to feel her absence
over those two days.

393
00:22:04,390 --> 00:22:06,100
I'm off. Bye.

394
00:22:12,900 --> 00:22:14,100
Her absence?

395
00:22:16,840 --> 00:22:18,040
As if.

396
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:21,850
You were too slow, so I left.

397
00:22:21,850 --> 00:22:24,210
Did it upset you that much?
You look like you'd cry.

398
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:27,450
What? What are you doing?

399
00:22:28,320 --> 00:22:29,550
(Chairman Gong Nan Sook)

400
00:22:30,320 --> 00:22:31,920
You! Jin Tae Seok!

401
00:22:32,860 --> 00:22:34,960
You've been through a lot,
Gong Nan Sook.

402
00:22:35,860 --> 00:22:37,130
My friend.

403
00:22:40,930 --> 00:22:42,500
Friend, my foot.

404
00:22:43,500 --> 00:22:46,840
- You'd send your friend to jail?
- You think I was being serious?

405
00:22:48,140 --> 00:22:50,310
You were pointlessly scheming behind
Joo Ha Neul and Cha Jung Won.

406
00:22:50,740 --> 00:22:53,780
All I did was land one punch
to tell you to knock it off,

407
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:55,010
and you're getting
all worked up over that.

408
00:22:55,080 --> 00:23:00,050
You have so many skeletons
you fear Ha Neul will land a hit,

409
00:23:00,050 --> 00:23:03,420
so you're hiding in the background,
but do you think I don't know that?

410
00:23:03,490 --> 00:23:06,990
When it comes to guilt,
we're in the same boat.

411
00:23:07,220 --> 00:23:11,360
It's the pot
calling the kettle black.

412
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:15,430
That's rich coming from you.

413
00:23:15,770 --> 00:23:17,400
For a punk like you,

414
00:23:17,470 --> 00:23:19,940
there's only one way
to make you pay.

415
00:23:20,800 --> 00:23:22,270
Go after your kid.

416
00:23:24,040 --> 00:23:26,410
I told you to leave
Se Mi out of this.

417
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:30,250
What good is Jin Se Mi to me?
She's so weak and pathetic.

418
00:23:30,350 --> 00:23:32,420
But Jin Se Hoon is different.

419
00:23:32,950 --> 00:23:35,450
And the nerve of him,
did he cast out my Young Chae?

420
00:23:36,150 --> 00:23:39,220
He's Yeong Ran's son.
I won't even bat an eye at that.

421
00:23:40,690 --> 00:23:43,690
So stop with these
pointless games...

422
00:23:44,130 --> 00:23:45,600
and get back on my side.

423
00:23:45,660 --> 00:23:49,830
Cut the nonsense and get lost!
Don't even think of seeing me again!

424
00:23:50,670 --> 00:23:52,770
Call me when you've cooled off!

425
00:23:55,710 --> 00:23:56,710
Darn it.

426
00:23:57,270 --> 00:23:59,880
Manager Gu, where's the coarse salt?

427
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:01,310
He's such bad luck.
I should do something...

428
00:24:01,380 --> 00:24:02,950
We don't have salt at the office.

429
00:24:03,080 --> 00:24:05,050
What? Then go buy some, quick!

430
00:24:05,120 --> 00:24:06,120
Right away.

431
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:11,420
He's so infuriating. Darn him.

432
00:24:13,990 --> 00:24:15,460
Hey, do it right!

433
00:24:15,460 --> 00:24:16,830
Good grief.

434
00:24:24,170 --> 00:24:25,540
- Manager Gu.
- Yes?

435
00:24:25,540 --> 00:24:28,170
- I need you to look into something.
- What can I do for you?

436
00:24:28,440 --> 00:24:32,840
Jin Se Hoon's late birth mother,
Jo Yeong Ran, was it?

437
00:24:33,140 --> 00:24:36,180
Find out if she was seeing other men
besides Jin Tae Seok.

438
00:24:36,280 --> 00:24:37,850
May I ask why you're digging
into a dead woman's past?

439
00:24:39,450 --> 00:24:42,320
Didn't I say not to ask questions?
Have you forgotten already?

440
00:24:42,620 --> 00:24:45,760
Understood. No questions asked,
I'll do as you say.

441
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:47,090
- Get going.
- Yes, ma'am.

442
00:24:49,760 --> 00:24:53,500
If my hunch is right,
things are about to get interesting.

443
00:24:57,030 --> 00:24:58,200
This is good.

444
00:25:03,840 --> 00:25:05,540
You found something already?

445
00:25:05,610 --> 00:25:08,450
I've been a lot quicker
and smarter lately, ma'am.

446
00:25:08,510 --> 00:25:09,810
I don't have all day. Spit it out.

447
00:25:09,810 --> 00:25:12,780
At Vice President Jin's
mother's nursing home,

448
00:25:12,850 --> 00:25:15,220
there was a man
who was a regular visitor.

449
00:25:15,890 --> 00:25:16,890
A man?

450
00:25:16,950 --> 00:25:20,720
He wasn't family or a relative,
but he visited for ten years.

451
00:25:20,860 --> 00:25:24,660
He was handsome, very devoted,
and even helped nurse her.

452
00:25:24,730 --> 00:25:27,530
Stop beating around the bush
and get to the point.

453
00:25:27,630 --> 00:25:29,170
They were lovers, apparently.

454
00:25:29,570 --> 00:25:32,840
According to her caregiver,
he even came to the funeral.

455
00:25:33,200 --> 00:25:37,570
So you're saying
Jin Se Hoon's mother had an affair?

456
00:25:38,910 --> 00:25:40,080
What?

457
00:25:40,080 --> 00:25:41,780
I'm not sure about that.

458
00:25:41,980 --> 00:25:44,810
This is the most interesting news
I've heard in a long time.

459
00:25:45,250 --> 00:25:46,720
I need to confirm this for myself.

460
00:25:47,480 --> 00:25:48,750
Wait a minute.

461
00:25:53,290 --> 00:25:54,520
Did you see Se Hoon?

462
00:25:54,520 --> 00:25:56,430
That's not important right now.

463
00:25:56,560 --> 00:25:58,730
What's more important than this?

464
00:25:58,730 --> 00:25:59,760
Just listen to me.

465
00:26:00,060 --> 00:26:03,330
Se Hoon casting you aside
could be a blessing in disguise.

466
00:26:03,600 --> 00:26:05,440
What? Mom!

467
00:26:05,640 --> 00:26:10,110
Jin Se Hoon might not be
Jin Tae Seok's biological son.

468
00:26:14,780 --> 00:26:16,410
Now it's your time to make a move.

469
00:26:16,410 --> 00:26:17,580
Quietly.

470
00:26:23,690 --> 00:26:25,760
If Se Hoon isn't
his father's biological son,

471
00:26:26,590 --> 00:26:28,190
does that mean he could lose
his position as heir?

472
00:26:30,130 --> 00:26:31,130
Wait, hold on.

473
00:26:31,760 --> 00:26:34,300
Then that means he and Cha Jung Won
aren't actually related at all.

474
00:26:36,500 --> 00:26:38,800
What if Se Hoon decides
to go back to Cha Jung Won?

475
00:26:41,640 --> 00:26:44,010
No. Absolutely not.

476
00:27:01,660 --> 00:27:04,660
I promise I'll find wild raspberries
for you later.

477
00:27:04,790 --> 00:27:06,360
It's okay. I like blueberries, too.

478
00:27:08,330 --> 00:27:10,830
A Reum, it's extra yummy
because Daddy got it for you, isn't it?

479
00:27:13,700 --> 00:27:16,370
I'm the one who kicked her out.
That was just so random.

480
00:27:18,310 --> 00:27:19,680
Did I just pop into your head?

481
00:27:23,910 --> 00:27:25,920
Are you going to kick me out again
for showing up uninvited?

482
00:27:26,180 --> 00:27:28,390
I just don't get you.
How can you be so...

483
00:27:28,520 --> 00:27:29,990
I'm hungry. Let's eat.

484
00:27:39,830 --> 00:27:40,830
It's good, isn't it?

485
00:27:41,160 --> 00:27:42,170
Surprisingly, yes.

486
00:27:42,730 --> 00:27:45,900
I just never pictured you cooking.

487
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:50,440
Tell me about it.
I'm used to others cooking for me.

488
00:27:53,410 --> 00:27:56,910
One risotto isn't going to make
all our problems disappear.

489
00:27:57,180 --> 00:27:58,180
I know.

490
00:27:59,780 --> 00:28:01,320
You didn't miss me at all?

491
00:28:01,550 --> 00:28:02,920
Don't be ridiculous.

492
00:28:03,190 --> 00:28:05,690
I'm asking
if you felt my absence at all.

493
00:28:12,800 --> 00:28:14,030
Just imagine...

494
00:28:15,270 --> 00:28:17,530
what it would have been like
if A Reum had been born.

495
00:28:20,300 --> 00:28:21,670
I used to imagine it all the time.

496
00:28:22,470 --> 00:28:25,440
You and me,
raising our child together.

497
00:28:28,650 --> 00:28:30,080
Please, just give me
one more chance.

498
00:28:30,910 --> 00:28:34,080
This time, I really want to have
a child that looks just like you.

499
00:28:41,260 --> 00:28:42,260
By the way,

500
00:28:43,390 --> 00:28:46,130
do a father and child
with the same blood type...

501
00:28:46,130 --> 00:28:47,330
have similar characteristics?

502
00:28:48,570 --> 00:28:50,930
You're a lot like your father.

503
00:28:51,400 --> 00:28:52,400
Hardly.

504
00:28:53,300 --> 00:28:56,310
I'm not as ruthless as my father.

505
00:28:57,470 --> 00:28:58,780
What's your blood type?

506
00:28:59,480 --> 00:29:00,580
Took you long enough to ask.

507
00:29:01,110 --> 00:29:02,110
I'm type A.

508
00:29:04,010 --> 00:29:06,320
But your father is B-negative.

509
00:29:07,220 --> 00:29:10,520
Does that mean
your biological mother was type AB?

510
00:29:12,660 --> 00:29:15,490
Why the sudden obsession
with blood types?

511
00:29:16,060 --> 00:29:18,230
Wait, are you Rh-negative?

512
00:29:19,060 --> 00:29:20,060
No.

513
00:29:28,100 --> 00:29:29,910
Don't ask any questions.

514
00:29:30,070 --> 00:29:32,980
Just get a DNA test done
for Jin Se Hoon and Jin Tae Seok.

515
00:29:32,980 --> 00:29:34,040
Understand?

516
00:29:38,650 --> 00:29:40,650
Should I go back to my mother's?

517
00:29:44,690 --> 00:29:46,920
Or is it okay if I just stay here?

518
00:29:49,390 --> 00:29:50,390
Do whatever you want.

519
00:30:29,700 --> 00:30:31,700
You think Young Chae is trying to...

520
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:34,070
get a DNA test on Jin Tae Seok
and Jin Se Hoon?

521
00:30:35,810 --> 00:30:36,810
I'm positive.

522
00:30:52,560 --> 00:30:53,560
What are you talking about?

523
00:30:54,260 --> 00:30:57,930
There's a chance Se Hoon isn't
Jin Tae Seok's biological son?

524
00:30:59,560 --> 00:31:01,030
If that's true,

525
00:31:01,530 --> 00:31:03,830
does this change
how we get our revenge?

526
00:31:08,400 --> 00:31:10,640
Of course, it has to change.

527
00:31:12,180 --> 00:31:14,680
Whether we completely
destroy Jin Se Hoon...

528
00:31:15,210 --> 00:31:18,380
or use him as a weapon
against Jin Tae Seok,

529
00:31:19,650 --> 00:31:22,920
we need to decide on
a clear path forward.

530
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:40,440
Kunhyang Group...

531
00:31:41,270 --> 00:31:44,170
is no longer run by Jin Tae Seok.
I, Han Hye Ra, am now in charge.

532
00:31:45,640 --> 00:31:46,840
And my bloodline...

533
00:31:49,750 --> 00:31:51,550
will be the ones
to inherit Kunhyang Group.

534
00:32:02,430 --> 00:32:05,430
(A Graceful Liar)

535
00:32:27,520 --> 00:32:29,650
- When does the trial start?
- Where's Manager Hwang?

536
00:32:29,720 --> 00:32:31,690
He said he'd be here in time
for the witness testimony.

537
00:32:31,750 --> 00:32:34,360
- His phone is turned off, too.
- Do you think something's wrong?

538
00:32:34,420 --> 00:32:36,860
Can we really trust these results?

539
00:32:37,090 --> 00:32:38,090
Is there any proof?

540
00:32:38,160 --> 00:32:40,960
Until now, I thought Se Hoon
was the heir to Kunhyang Group.

541
00:32:41,130 --> 00:32:44,030
Jin Se Hoon is completely useless.

542
00:32:44,430 --> 00:32:46,040
I have to get Young Chae
to divorce him.

543
00:32:49,810 --> 00:32:51,840
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
